584
01:11:39,620 --> 01:11:44,899
<i>Oh, our lost loved ones.</i>

585
01:11:46,900 --> 01:11:52,619
<i>We sleep and stay near Babylon.</i>

586
01:11:52,620 --> 01:11:55,863
<i>We sleep and stay.</i>

587
01:12:00,540 --> 01:12:06,343
<i>Losing our sons is
like losing our souls.</i>

588
01:12:11,300 --> 01:12:17,103
<i>We only want him to walk
with the other boys.</i>

589
01:12:17,900 --> 01:12:23,703
<i>They put their jackets
over their shoulders.</i>

590
01:12:24,860 --> 01:12:26,099
Grandma...

591
01:12:26,100 --> 01:12:28,376
I don't want to be a soldier.

592
01:12:28,380 --> 01:12:31,736
I want to become a musician,
like Dad.

593
01:16:28,020 --> 01:16:29,181
Grandma?

594
01:16:29,940 --> 01:16:31,305
Grandma?

595
01:16:31,940 --> 01:16:34,739
Grandma, I'm going to ask
that man.

596
01:16:49,420 --> 01:16:54,699
Ibrahim! My son, where are you?

597
01:16:56,340 --> 01:16:59,819
He's not here.
Most bodies have no ID.

598
01:16:59,820 --> 01:17:02,539
There's no equipment
to identify them.

599
01:17:02,540 --> 01:17:05,459
New mass graves were found.
You should check there.

600
01:17:05,460 --> 01:17:07,462
One minute.

601
01:17:19,220 --> 01:17:23,100
Oh my son.
Oh my son, I miss you.

602
01:17:26,500 --> 01:17:31,336
I looked everywhere for you.

603
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:46,936
The man said that he's not here.

604
01:17:47,700 --> 01:17:51,421
They found another mass grave,
we should go there.

605
01:17:52,260 --> 01:17:54,183
Grandma, please.

606
01:17:55,900 --> 01:17:58,699
Please, Grandma...

607
01:18:03,700 --> 01:18:06,779
Grandma, look at this.
His name is Omar.

608
01:18:06,780 --> 01:18:08,020
Grandma!

609
01:18:13,900 --> 01:18:15,743
Grandma, this one's called Salem.

610
01:18:16,540 --> 01:18:17,974
Grandma!

611
01:18:25,460 --> 01:18:27,497
Grandma, this one is called Jawad!

612
01:18:33,460 --> 01:18:37,055
